picoctf Operation Oni writeup

1.just use "gzip -d filename" , "binwalk -e filename" to extract this img file 

2.and we can go in to that dir and use "find | grep "key_file"" or "find | grep "ssh""

3.we can see there is a id_ed25519 file in the root dir , this might be the key

4.use this file key to connect the server (ssh -i id_ed25519 -p 51006 ctf-player@saturn.picoctf.net) but you will find there is a warning

5.so we need to change the permissions to 600 or other low permissions (chmod 600 id_ed25519)

6.connect it again , we can see a flag.txt

7.get flag!
